Saw a good friend who had been away for a few years and it's just so exhilarating to give him a big hug and shake his hand, both of us laughing like retards. Friendship is such a cool thing, it makes time and space irrelevant. Sorta following St. Velimirovic friendship is prayer.

In that he said if you are unable to pray the normal way even thinking of a person in a loving and positive way counts as a lesser prayer and if you are good friends w/ someone you want the best for him so you tend to think about him in that exact positive and loving way. Or her.

Miguel Serrano says in his "Imitation of The Truth" essay on military cybernetics that the "hidden world power" global elite despises forests partly because they make satellite espionage difficult so many forest fires are intentionally started by them. He's sorta the anti-Aquino.

St. Amphilochios of Patmos saying the 11th commandment is to "love the trees" and telling people to plant pine trees as repentance for confessed sins. St. Iakovos who planted a forest said the devil starts forest fires out of envy. The world is a pro-tree and anti-tree total war.
A Series of Unfortunate Events talks about this.

Discussing some Tolkien letters, a friend of mine pointed out the "mnemotechnical" aspect of fantasy: organizing known facts of the real world in new arrangement may even lead to new facts being discovered. Sometimes a memory palace contains objects one did not put there himself.

The imagination is able to explore not only the "real" world, but fantasty worlds connected to it. I would describe it as taking the pieces of a mosaic and re-arranging them in a different configuration then filling the gaps that may have formed using premonition or intuition.

I am reminded of one Neon Genesis Evangelion hallucination where the protagonist sees an alternative reality where him and the other Eva pilots are regular schoolchildren in a peaceful world. If one explores this sub-reality deep, he will discover new facts about his own reality.
